# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# paper-age — easy and secure paper backups of secrets (Rust, 594★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/matiaskorhonen/paper-age
# author : Matias Korhonen (matiaskorhonen, me@matiaskorhonen.fi)
# license: MIT
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from src/cli.rs
# on the paper-age v1.5.0 tip — clap-derive `Args` struct with
# `clap-verbosity-flag` for the verbosity scaffold and the `PageSize`
# ValueEnum from src/page.rs.
#
# Direct deps from Cargo.toml (selected):
#   printpdf       0.9.1  ← canonical Rust pure-Rust PDF generation
#                           library (this axis) — by Felix Schütt
#                           (fschutt/printpdf); no system dependencies,
#                           no Cairo/libharu/wkhtmltopdf shell-out,
#                           pure-Rust generation from layout primitives
#                           with embedded font subsetting.  Pulled in
#                           with the `text_layout` feature for the
#                           paragraph-level wrapping used by paper-age's
#                           document body.
#   age            0.11.2  (asymmetric/symmetric age encryption — Filippo
#                           Valsorda's age format, Rust port maintained
#                           by the str4d collective)
#   qrcode         0.14.1  (QR code generation — the ciphertext is rendered
#                           as a QR code at the center of the page; scan
#                           with any reader to recover the bytes)
#   clap (derive) + clap-verbosity-flag (the canonical clap verbosity
#                           scaffold by clap-rs/clap-verbosity-flag,
#                           giving -v / -vv / -vvv / -q / -qq for logger
#                           level selection)
#   rpassword              (interactive passphrase prompt without echo)
#   exitcode               (canonical exit-code constants — DATAERR,
#                           CANTCREAT, NOINPUT, SOFTWARE)
#   env_logger             (logger backend)
#
# paper-age creates a single-page PDF backup of a small secret (≤ ~1.9 KB
# of plaintext input): the input is age-encrypted with a passphrase,
# the ciphertext is rendered as a QR code at the center of the page,
# and a paper-friendly layout adds a title + notes line for the
# passphrase reminder.  Print the PDF, store the paper in a safe
# location, and decrypt later by scanning the QR + entering the
# passphrase.  Intended for low-frequency backup of crypto wallet seed
# phrases, password manager master passwords, SSH keys, etc.
#
# === AXIS 174 OPENER — pure-language PDF generation libraries ============
# Axis position: Rust=229 OPENS Axis 174 at slot 1/0/0.  Canonical Rust
# pure-language PDF generation library is `printpdf` by Felix Schütt
# (fschutt/printpdf) — no system C dependencies (no Cairo, no libharu,
# no wkhtmltopdf shell-out), generates PDFs directly from Rust layout
# primitives with embedded TTF font subsetting.  Used by paper-age,
# thClaws (LLM agent's PdfCreate tool), genpdf, leroycep/mdproof,
# theiskaa/markdown2pdf, and most modern Rust CLIs that need PDF
# output without dragging in a system PDF stack.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=229     ← THIS FILE              (axis 174 OPENS, slot 1/0/0)
#   Go=229       ← next round              (axis 174 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=229  ← round after             (axis 174 CLOSES at triple-229, slot 1/1/1)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_paper-age() {
    _arguments -s -S \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[print version]' \
        '(-t --title)'{-t,--title=}'[page title, max 64 characters (default PaperAge)]:title:' \
        '(-n --notes-label)'{-n,--notes-label=}'[notes label below the QR code, max 32 characters (default Passphrase:)]:label:' \
        '--skip-notes-line[skip the notes placeholder line (e.g. Passphrase: ________)]' \
        '(-o --output)'{-o,--output=}'[output file name (default out.pdf; use - for STDOUT)]:output PDF:_files -g "*.pdf"' \
        '(-s --page-size)'{-s,--page-size=}'[paper size (default A4)]:size:(A4 Letter)' \
        '(-f --force)'{-f,--force}'[overwrite the output file if it already exists]' \
        '(-g --grid)'{-g,--grid}'[draw a grid pattern for debugging layout issues]' \
        '(- *)--fonts-license[print out the license for the embedded fonts (IBM Plex Mono) and exit]' \
        '(-v --verbose)'{-v,--verbose}'[increase verbosity (repeatable: -v=info, -vv=debug, -vvv=trace)]' \
        '(-q --quiet)'{-q,--quiet}'[decrease verbosity (repeatable)]' \
        '*:file to read (defaults to stdin; max ~1.9 KiB):_files'
}

_paper-age "$@"
